From: PureCloak Authors <purecloak-dev@purecloak.org>
Date: Sat, 20 Jun 2026 12:05:00 +0800
Subject: Add deterministic canvas noise to toDataURL/toBlob and ImageData constructor

Under PureCloak, inject deterministic ±1 noise into ~0.1% of RGB
channels in toDataURL, toBlob, and ImageData() constructor outputs.
This complements the getImageData noise (Patch 0008) to cover all
canvas export and pixel-read paths.

The noise is applied by reading the canvas snapshot pixels into a
writable copy, applying noise, and creating a new image for encoding.
For the ImageData constructor, noise is injected directly into the
allocated byte buffer before wrapping it in the ImageData object.

No BUILDFLAG guards are needed since patches only apply during
PureCloak builds.

---
